input.prompt:
Compare the refactored version of /view-split-lease against live production using Playwright MCP.

**Steps to execute:**
1. Navigate to LIVE: https://split.lease/view-split-lease
2. Wait 2 seconds: browser_wait_for(time=2)
3. Take LIVE screenshot: browser_take_screenshot(fullPage=true, filename="live-view-split-lease.png")
4. Capture LIVE console errors: browser_console_messages(level="error")
5. Navigate to DEV: http://localhost:8010/view-split-lease
6. Wait 2 seconds: browser_wait_for(time=2)
7. Take DEV screenshot: browser_take_screenshot(fullPage=true, filename="dev-view-split-lease.png")
8. Capture DEV console errors: browser_console_messages(level="error")

**Comparison criteria:**
- Visual parity: Compare layout structure, interactive elements, content rendering
- Ignore: Pixel-perfect differences, different data values (if layout is identical)
- Flag: Any missing elements, layout shifts, broken components

**Return ONLY a JSON object:**
{
  "visualParity": "PASS" | "FAIL",
  "issues": ["list of visual differences"],
  "consoleErrors": ["list of console error messages from both environments"],
  "explanation": "Brief reasoning for the verdict"
}

Use Playwright MCP tools (browser_navigate, browser_wait_for, browser_take_screenshot, browser_console_messages) to complete this task.
